"text","text":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then any call to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_set_property()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" results"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If they did pass [explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then this signal is emitted only","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when they explicitly call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and common practice is to do that only when the value has actually changed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This signal is typically used to obtain change notification for a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"single property, by specifying the property name as a detail in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_connect()"},{"type":"text","text":" call, like this:"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["g_signal_connect (text_view->buffer, \"notify::paste-target-list\",","                  G_CALLBACK (gtk_text_view_target_list_notify),","                  text_view)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to note that you must use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"#class@GObj